commText: Jaiswal and Buttler are at the crease. Jaiswal is on strike. Topley will open the attack
Topley to Jaiswal, no run, full and hint of away movement, Jaiswal prods forward and defends to the off-side
Topley to Jaiswal, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Topley to Jaiswal, out Caught by Maxwell!! That's a great start for RCB. Topley strikes with his second ball. Jaiswal's not having a great start to the season. He decides to walk down the pitch and Topley sees that, shortens the length and generates extra bounce, Jaiswal still goes for the pull and only manages a top-edge, Maxwell settles under it near mid-off and takes it safely. Jaiswal c Maxwell b Topley 0(2)
Jaiswal vs LA Fast in IPL 2024 Runs: 28 Balls: 20 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 9.33 SR: 140
Sanju Samson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Topley to Samson, no run, uhhh! Nearly chopped on. Back of a length and angled across, Samson tries to ride the bounce and defend, but ekes out an inside edge wide of leg-stump
Topley to Samson, no run, I0$ good length ball on leg, Samson turns it with soft hands to mid-wicket
Topley to Samson, 1 run, I0$ delivery that is too straight, Samson flicks it wide of mid-on and opens RR's account

Topley to Buttler, no run, peach! The bounce saving Buttler on this occasion. Nips in but the length is fraction short, Buttler is rooted to the crease and cut into half, the ball beats the inside edge and flies over the stumps
Yash Dayal, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Yash Dayal to Samson, no run, good length ball on off, Samson is stuck to the crease and brings his bat down, ekes out an inside edge onto the pad
Slip for Dayal as well
Yash Dayal to Samson, FOUR, shot! All timing from Samson. Angled across him and he uses that to his advantage, just opens the bat face and eases it square on the off-side. The ball races away..
Slip taken out and the off-side is strenghtened
Yash Dayal to Samson, no run, slanted outside off, Samson goes chasing and is beaten on the outside edge
Third man brought in and point sent back
Yash Dayal to Samson, no run, on a length and outside off, Samson crunches the drive and picks out cover
Yash Dayal to Samson, no run, fullish delivery on off, Samson defends it back to Dayal and he stops in his followthrough
Yash Dayal to Samson, FOUR, boundary to end the over. Dayal goes short of length and Samson is quick to pounce, pulls it in front of square and the ball bounces just once before crossing the rope
Topley to Buttler, no run, I0$ good length ball and bit of inward movement, Buttler defends to mid-wicket

STAT: Samson completed 4,000 IPL runs with his first boundary today. Of the 16 players to have done so till date, his strike-rate of 137.23 is bettered only by AB de Villiers (151.68), Chris Gayle (148.96) and David Warner (140).
Topley to Buttler, no run, short and keeps going away with the angle, Buttler goes chasing after it and does not reach. Very close to being a wide
Topley to Buttler, 1 run, swinging into the pads, Buttler flicks and there's protection in the deep, just a single

Topley to Samson, FOUR, wow! That really is a wow shot from Samson. Nothing much wrong with the delivery - good length ball on off, Samson brings his bat down fluently and just pushes it down the ground. The timing is such that Faf's chase from mid-off is a valiant one
Topley to Samson, 1 run, low full toss on the pads, Samson flicks to deep square leg
Topley to Buttler, 1 run, I0$ back of a length delivery, Buttler looks to work it into the leg-side and gets an inside edge onto the thigh pad
Mohammed Siraj, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Siraj to Buttler, FOUR, trademark Buttler and that should get him going. First ball from Siraj and Buttler walks across his stumps, picks up the back of a length delivery and laps it right back over Karthik

Siraj to Buttler, 2 runs, brilliant effort from Green but the ball does not stick. Fullish delivery and Buttler throws the kitchen sink on the drive, slices it over the off-side field and three fielders give chase, Green is the one who gets there with a dive and he also goes with both hands, but the ball does not stick

Siraj to Buttler, no run, mix-up but no harm done. Buttler eases it into the off-side and wants a single, Samson is not interested and is also ball watching, Buttler is halfway down but the ball was between cover and cover-point, Kohli and Green make the stop but can't gather the ball cleanly, allowing Buttler to get back
Siraj to Buttler, 1 run, in-angler on off and middle, Buttler knocks it firmly to the right of mid-on and Topley with the stop
Siraj to Samson, 1 run, fullish delivery around off, Samson drives towards mid-off and hurries to the other end
Siraj to Buttler, 1 run, short ball bowled into the wicket, Buttler is rushed on the pull but he plays it down to deep mid-wicket
Yash Dayal [1.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack
Yash Dayal to Buttler, FOUR, neatly done! I0$ delivery angled across the right hander, Buttler opens the bat face and steers it wide of short third. He played that right from off-stump line
Yash Dayal to Buttler, no run, I0$ full delivery close to off, Buttler slices the drive to point
Yash Dayal to Buttler, no run, now walks down the wicket and is beaten by the away slant, he has a tentative push and is lucky not to have nicked it
Yash Dayal to Buttler, no run, once again plays the steer but this is straight to short third

Yash Dayal to Buttler, FOUR, I0$ short of length delivery and hint of width on offer, that is enough for Buttler to cash in as he gets on top of the bounce and cracks it in front of square. No one in the deep on the off-side to stop that
Yash Dayal to Buttler, 1 run, leg-lined delivery and Buttler flicks to deep mid-wicket, retains strike

Highlights (1-5 overs) -> Topley strikes in his first over, Jaiswal goes for a duck -> Samson off to a positive start, hits a couple of boundaries against Yash -> Buttler gets a life as Green puts down a tough catch -> RR off to a scratchy start, 34/1 after 5 overs
Mayank Dagar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Mayank Dagar to Buttler, FOUR, Buttler looking in ominous touch. This is fraction short around off, Buttler stays leg-side and cracks it in front of square on the off-side, Maxwell had a few yards to cover and he's beaten by the pace on the ball
Mayank Dagar to Buttler, no run, slower and at the stumps, Buttler defends it to the off-side
Mayank Dagar to Buttler, FOUR, Buttler motoring along now. He quickly latches onto the short of length delivery and pulls it over mid-on, the ball goes on the half volley into the ad cushions

Mayank Dagar to Buttler, SIX, that's gone all the way. Buttler is back. Dagar under pressure. Flighted delivery and it is overcooked, Buttler clears his front leg and smacks it straight down the ground

Mayank Dagar to Buttler, FOUR, Dagar has ruined the start for RCB. 18 off the over and still a ball left. Short and outside off, Buttler cracks it in front of square and pierces a packed off-side field

Mayank Dagar to Buttler, 2 runs, 20 off the over. What it has done is - RR have finished the powerplay strongly and it has also got Buttler going. Quicker and fuller, Buttler drives wide of long-off and picks up a brace
Cameron Green, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Green to Samson, no run, tight good length delivery, angling into middle, nudged to mid-wicket
STAT: Buttler has scored more runs today than he did across his last six innings in the IPL (35 off 50, including three ducks).
Green to Samson, 2 runs, short of length and angling into the pads, Samson miscues the flick but places it wide of deep mid-wicket, to his right, gets back for two
Green to Samson, 1 run, short of length on the stumps, Samson makes room and punches wide of cover, single easily done
Green to Buttler, 1 run, short of length on off, tucked to the vacant square leg region

Most balls faced in an IPL innings 73 - Brendon McCullum (KKR) vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2008 73 - Manish Pandey (RCB) vs Deccan Chargers, Centurion, 2009 72 - Virat Kohli (RCB) vs RR, Jaipur, 2024 70 - KL Rahul (PBKS) vs RR, Jaipur, 2018 70 - Quinton de Kock (LSG) vs KKR, Mumbai DYP, 2022
Green to Samson, 2 runs, short of length and Samson pulls over mid-wicket, did not get hold of it, but wide of deep mid-wicket and another couple
Green to Samson, wide, short of length and flies to Karthik but it's a wide, Samson flicks and misses, almost burst through DK's gloves
Green to Samson, 2 runs, fullish just outside off, Samson drives with a full face, again nice timing and two more to long-on
Himanshu Sharma, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Himanshu Sharma to Buttler, 1 run, flat legbreak on a good length on off, punched to long-off

Himanshu Sharma to Samson, FOUR, drags the legbreak short outside off, Samson pulls wide of mid-wicket, Kohli at deep mid-wicket and Dagar at long-on leave it to each other, it goes away for four. Sloppy stuff from RCB
Himanshu Sharma to Samson, 2 runs, long square boundaries here, short legbreak outside off, cut wide of sweeper cover and they come back for two

Himanshu Sharma to Samson, FOUR, Kohli does not catch that at deep mid-wicket. Dragged down this googly, Samson pulls and Kohli runs and dives forward but the ball slips through the hands, did not even touch them. But definitely catchable that, once Kohli got there
Himanshu Sharma to Samson, 1 run, this stays low, from a good length, Samson adjusts and bunts to long-on off the back foot
Himanshu Sharma to Buttler, 2 runs, tossed up full legbreak outside off, Buttler gets forward and drives wide of Maxi at long-off, for two
Timeout! That last over in the powerplay from Dagar has changed the complexion of the game. RR getting runs easily and RCB need to break this partnership quickly. Both batters look very much at ease.
Live visuals show dew forming on the grass. That is bad news for RCB.
Green to Samson, no run, full outside off, Samson leans forward to drive well but straight to the fielder at cover

Green to Samson, 1 run, premeditated and Samson nearly gets into trouble. A short of length delivery outside off, he shuffles across to scoop and gloves it on to the body, Buttler calls him through for a quick single
Green to Buttler, FOUR, mid-off is up and Buttler has laced that wide of cover. Fullish outside off, Buttler gets forward and drives on the rise, was the slower ball off-cutter as replays show

Green to Buttler, 1 run, could Yash Dayal have done better? A short ball at Buttler who pulls and it was in the air for a long time, Dayal does not go for the catch at fine-leg, instead he opts to take it on the bounce, a definite chance that
Green to Samson, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on off, Samson makes room and drives wide of mid-off
Green to Buttler, no run, skiddy back of a length delivery outside off, Buttler pulls and misses, beaten for pace
Mohammed Siraj [1.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack
Siraj to Samson, 1 run, full outside off, driven on the rise to long-on
Siraj to Buttler, 1 run, full outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Siraj to Samson, SIX, poor ball and Samson has upper-cut that over deep backward point, short and wide outside off, Samson puts it away on his tiptoes
Siraj to Samson, 1 run, nearly the low full-toss is above the waist, flicked away to deep mid-wicket
Siraj to Buttler, 1 run, 50 for Buttler. He is back. A short delivery on off, pulled to deep square leg
Siraj to Samson, 1 run, full outside off, driven to sweeper cover

Highlights (6-10 overs) -> Buttler scores 20 runs against Dagar in the 6th over -> RR's chase back on track as they finish the powerplay at 54/1 -> Buttler and Samson dealing in boundaries, a solid partnership building -> Rajasthan placed comfortably in the chase. 95/1 after 10
Mayank Dagar [1.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack

Mayank Dagar to Samson, no run, confusion and both batters get away, good length on off, punched wide of Faf at cover, the throw is to DK, had it gone to Mayank Dagar, Buttler was gone, he was halfway down the track, tracks back and dives to get in. Another half-a-chance gone
Mayank Dagar to Samson, no run, Samson comes down the track and gets too close to the pitch, bunts it off a thick inside-edge to short mid-wicket
Mayank Dagar to Samson, FOUR, that is Samson at his very best. Makes room, takes it on a good length on the stumps, lofts over extra-cover, no chance for sweeper cover
Mayank Dagar to Samson, no run, Samson comes down the track and drives on the rise, but straight to the fielder at cover
Mayank Dagar to Samson, SIX, 50 for Samson. What a shot to get there. He gives the charge and makes room to free the arms, goes inside-out, over extra-cover and flies all the way, flat hit
Mayank Dagar to Samson, FOUR, dragged down on leg-stump, Samson goes on the back foot and pulls wide of Siraj at deep square leg, was in the air but wide of him, one bounce over the ropes
Himanshu Sharma [1.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Himanshu Sharma to Buttler, SIX, runs flowing now. It's a tossed up legbreak on the stumps, too full and Buttler clears his front leg to loft straight down the ground
Himanshu Sharma to Buttler, 1 run, slower and tossed up on leg-stump, flicked to deep square leg

Himanshu Sharma to Samson, FOUR, nothing working for RCB now. This is a good length legbreak outside off, fraction short and Samson uses his hands to steer that through backward point, long chase for sweeper cover and he gives up
Two or more century partnerships for RR in the IPL (any wicket) \n3 - Jos Buttler and Sanju Samson \n2 - Graeme Smith and Swapnil Asnodkar
Himanshu Sharma to Samson, 2 runs, this googly is on a back of a length and on the middle and leg line, tucked wide of deep mid-wicket for an easy two
Himanshu Sharma to Samson, 1 run, short of length on off, tucked away to the deep mid-wicket region

Himanshu Sharma to Buttler, 1 run, flighted delivery full on the stumps, Buttler gets forward to drive, thick inside-edge to deep mid-wicket. DK seems excited for some reason, claps that ball from Himanshu Sharma, still 15 off that over
Yash Dayal [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Yash Dayal to Buttler, 1 run, slower ball on a good length on off, bunted through vacant mid-wicket
Yash Dayal to Samson, 1 run, seam-up good length just outside off, punched wide of Patidar at sweeper cover and he does well to keep it to one
Yash Dayal to Buttler, 2 runs, slower short ball on off, pulled wide of deep square leg and Maxwell can't prevent the 2nd, good aggressive running
Yash Dayal to Buttler, 2 runs, short on off, pulled wide of deep mid-wicket and now Kohli can't prevent the 2nd
Yash Dayal to Buttler, no run, went for the yorker, very full on the stumps, dug out to backward point

Yash Dayal to Buttler, SIX, incredible shot and even Buttler has a wry smile on his face. The back of the hand slower ball is short and wide outside off, Buttler was almost deceived, waited and waited before flat-batting it, long-off was in business, but it clears his leap and just as well. To generate such power from such a slower ball, what power and what wrists
11, 14, 15 and 12 from the last four overs. RR running away with this.
Reece Topley [2.0-0-8-1] is back into the attack
Topley to Samson, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, glided down to third man with an open face

Topley to Buttler, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, cut to backward point and Samson is halfway down, the throw is to the keeper's end and again the wrong end, no backing up and now they take the single. Sloppy all-around from RCB
Topley to Samson, 1 run, short of length outside off, cut to sweeper cover
Looks like RCB have given up already. Their body language is as down as it can be.
Topley to Buttler, wide, way outside off, wide of the tramline, left alone and wide taken
Topley to Buttler, no run, short of length and tight on the stumps, defended to backward point and a loud no from Buttler to Samson

Topley to Buttler, FOUR, pure timing. There is a short third man and backward point, short of length outside off, hint of width and steered expertly to the deep backward point fence, again sweeper cover is just a spectator
Topley to Buttler, 1 run, full on the stumps, Buttler shows the full face of the bat to drive to long-off
Mohammed Siraj [2.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
Siraj to Buttler, 1 run, full outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Siraj to Samson, 1 run, full outside off, driven to long-on
Siraj to Buttler, 1 run, dug in short outside off, pulled to deep mid-wicket
Siraj to Samson, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Siraj to Samson, out Caught by Yash Dayal!! Siraj gets Samson and smiles with fists clenched at the batter. A short delivery at the body, Samson miscues the pull and Dayal at deep backward square leg takes it just an inch from the cushions. The leg was tantalisingly close but he ensured that he was fine. Some respite for RCB. Samson c Yash Dayal b Siraj 69(42) [4s-8 6s-2]
Riyan Parag, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Siraj to Riyan Parag, no run, full on off, kept out
Siraj to Riyan Parag, FOUR, he is in fine form. A short of length delivery on off, Riyan Parag's confidence shows as he pulls dismissively over mid-wicket, slightly premeditated but he pulled it off

Highlights (11-15 overs) -> Mayank Dagar bowls another expensive over, concedes 14 runs -> Himanshu Sharma goes for 15 runs in the next over -> Runs coming thick and fast as RR inch closer to the target -> Samson and Buttler going strong, even Topley at the receiving end -> Siraj breaks the partnership, Samson is caught at deep backward square leg
Yash Dayal [3.0-0-29-0] is back into the attack
Yash Dayal to Buttler, 2 runs, slower ball full on the stumps, flicked wide of long-on and Maxwell with a diving stop, flicks it to Kohli at deep mid-wicket
Yash Dayal to Buttler, 1 run, full outside off, driven wide of cover
Yash Dayal to Riyan Parag, no run, another slower ball, fullish on the stumps, Riyan Parag with a forward defence
Yash Dayal to Riyan Parag, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Dayal to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Kohli!! Soft dismissal. A short of length delivery on off, whipped straight to the fielder at mid-wicket and Kohli does not drop that. Riyan Parag falls for a cheap score. It's the timeout as well. Riyan Parag c Kohli b Yash Dayal 4(4) [4s-1]
RR still very much in control of this chase despite losing two quick wickets. Can RCB spark something special from here?
Dhruv Jurel, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Yash Dayal to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, short of length outside off, dabbed down to third man and Dhruv Jurel is away
Kohli is off the field. He is seen having a chat with Andy Flower and Malolan Rangarajan.
Yash Dayal to Buttler, FOUR, full outside off, Buttler gets forward and drives with an open face, beats the diving short third man to his right, angled it beautifully past the fielder
Reece Topley [3.0-0-17-1] is back into the attack
Topley to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, short of length outside off, guided down to third man with an open face
Topley round the wicket.

Topley to Buttler, 3 runs, so so sloppy. A good length delivery on the stumps, nudged in front of long-on, the fielder charges and throws it well wide of Topley, no backing up and they take one more. Kohli can't bear to watch from the dugout
Topley to Dhruv Jurel, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Topley to Dhruv Jurel, out Caught by Karthik!! A leg-side strangle. Full down leg, Dhruv Jurel flicks and edges it behind to Karthik. DK does not even celebrate as Siraj is all happy near him. Dhruv Jurel walks off shaking his head. Dhruv Jurel c Karthik b Topley 2(3)
Shimron Hetmyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Topley to Hetmyer, 1 run, full outside off, driven wide of mid-off for one
Jos Buttler vs Yash Dayal in the IPL Runs: 92 Balls: 41 Dismissals: 0 SR: 224.39 4s/6s: 13/4
Topley to Buttler, 1 run, short outside off, pulled down to deep mid-wicket
Topley to Hetmyer, FOUR, there comes the inevitable boundary in the over. A short delivery outside off, pulled wide of deep square leg and deep mid-wicket, right into the gap
The only interest here is if Buttler can get to a 100? The game's as good as done.
Cameron Green [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Green to Buttler, 1 run, full on the stumps, Buttler stays leg-side and is almost opened up, thick leading-edge rolls to sweeper cover, all along the ground
Faf still adjusting the field. Green round the wicket.
Green to Hetmyer, no run, good length and tight on the stumps, defended
Green to Hetmyer, 1 run, short of length on off, tucked wide of mid-on

Green to Buttler, 2 runs, slower ball and following Buttler who makes room outside the leg-stump, tucked wide of deep mid-wicket and two more, Green is not happy, he is chuntering away, shaking his head. Maxi was the fielder
Green to Buttler, no run, short of length outside off, extra bounce, Buttler tries to cut late and misses
Green to Buttler, 1 run, short at Buttler who is outside the leg-stump, pulled to deep square leg
Buttler needs 8 for his 100 and 9 for the win. Couple of hits!
Mohammed Siraj [3.0-0-27-1] is back into the attack
Siraj to Buttler, no run, good yorker outside off, Buttler makes room and can't lay bat on ball
Siraj to Buttler, no run, now a good slower short ball, dug in and following Buttler who was arching back to glide, misses. Two dots in a row
Siraj to Buttler, 1 run, full on the stumps, drilled to mid-off and they take one
Kohli happy to watch the game from the dugout. Remember he held his leg while fielding a ball. Something of a niggle? Or just a precaution.

Siraj to Hetmyer, FOUR, swung away for four. Right between deep square leg and deep mid-wicket, length delivery on the stumps, heaved away in the air and kept Maxi at deep mid-wicket interested, but just wide of him
Short third man in. Long-on back.
Siraj to Hetmyer, wide, short and wide outside off, too short and wide, left alone, wide called. RCB have reviewed this. Making the game go deep. It is wide of the tramline and the wide call stays
Siraj to Hetmyer, 1 run, very full on the stumps, clipped to deep mid-wicket
The only way Buttler can get to a 100 is to to take a single here and then hit a six.
Siraj to Buttler, 1 run, short of length on off, Buttler goes too hard on the pull, thick inside-edge hits the right thigh and goes to short third man, they take the run. Scores level
1 to win and Buttler needs 6 for a 100. Green to bowl. Faf still setting the field. True competitor this man.

Green to Buttler, SIX, 100 for Buttler. RR win. He is happy, leaps and punches the air. Hugs Hetmyer. 100 in his 100th match bellows Ian Bishop on air. A short of length delivery on the stumps, Buttler pulls and does not get all of it, but it has the legs to clear the deep mid-wicket fence, just about and that will do. He had a chat with Hetmyer at the start of the over, with a smile on his face, mostly this scenario was discussed as well. As soon as the ball cleared the fence, Hetmyer was the man who was jumping up and down. The RR dugout are elated as well

23:07 Local Time, 17:37 GMT, 23:07 IST: This game may have gone to the last over but don't be fooled. This was as easy a chase as anything you might have seen in this format. Jaiswal went for a duck but then it was the Samson and Buttler show. They started off by attacking Dagar in the last over of the powerplay - that over set the tone and from there RR never looked back. Every over had a boundary when Samson and Buttler were going. The RR skipper went and a couple of cheap wickets followed. At the end the main interest was whether Buttler would get to a 100. Hetmyer's boundary in the penultimate over made it difficult but Buttler completed the job to end it in a blaze of glory. The wicket played better in the 2nd innings but it was the same old story for RCB. Their bowling lacked penetration and except Topley the others looked ordinary. Faf did not use Maxwell again, maybe considering the matchup against two right-handers in Samson and Buttler. The likes of Dagar and Himanshu barely made an impression. Familiar woes for RCB who slip to another loss. RR meanwhile remain unbeaten. Stay tuned for the presentation...

Faf du Plessis | RCB captain: I think we found the wicket tricky in the first innings. I thought 190 was a good score, think we could have added 10-15 runs max. Their spinners bowled well (in the middle overs), good decision by them to bowl first. With the dew batting got easier. Virat was playing well at the back end, with someone like Green coming in, you want to maximise those last overs. We tried to squeeze as hard as we can, but it was tricky to hit against the spinners. It was easier to hit the seamers. The pitch definitely got better, you could feel it, the ball was skidding along nicely. We were excellent in the first four overs. I think that 20 runs over (from Dagar) took the momentum away and shifted the pressure back on us. Not bowling Maxwell was because all right-handers were batting, so went to the left-handed spinner initially. With two right-handers at the crease, went to the left arm spinner and later got the leg spinner (Himanshu Sharma) into the attack. There was no point of being defensive, we needed wickets. When we got Jaiswal out, I didn't feel the need to go to Maxwell. Fielding was average, it's something we have spoken about, we'll work and try to improve. Not worried about catches, it's about showing intensity on the field.

Kumar Sangakkara: It was a good toss to win, pretty decisive to chase. RCB put us under pressure but the spinners and Burger got us back into the game. And the chase was clinical from Jos, Sanju and others. Everyone requires a chat but it does not need to be about cricket, form is a state of mind and Jos is the best white-ball opener in cricket for some time, you just have to let him be. Jaiswal has had a brilliant year or two not just for RR but also in international cricket, two bad innings does not make anyone a bad player, we know his quality and we just want him to bat long, it was nice to chase down this total without his contribution. There have been a lot of honest conversations, Sanju and I have connected well and have been speaking in the off season as well, the focus has been more inward than outward as a coaching staff this season.

Sanju Samson | RR captain: Anything below 190 with a little bit of dew, with the batting order we have, it was a good score to chase. Touchwood, a few games to go, they are doing well, four days of gap, allows people to recover, rest, train and allows you to come charged up for a game. Bowling is 9 and batting is 8.7. [on Buttler] Just about time, if he gets through the powerplay, and if he hits it, very happy for him and very happy for the team.

Jos Buttler | Player of the Match: Had a little bit of luck, did not time it well, just got over the rope, delighted with the win. However long you've played the game, you still have those anxieties and stresses. The mind is a powerful thing, just keep digging in, keep working hard and you need a little bit of luck along the way. At some point it will be okay and sometimes you have to tell yourself it will be okay. I did feel really good in the last game, even though I got 13. I had a really good tournament in South Africa, I just felt like I needed one innings to put that to bed. We started the season really well, we have been together now for three seasons, we have got a good thing going, but we need to keep working hard and keep the momentum going.
That's that for the night. Tomorrow we have a double-header coming up. We will be there as usual. Till then sleep well and sleep tight. Don't forget to keep cool as well. See ya.
